ortfolio/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/AudreyHird-Mockup-300x169.jpg 300w, http://localhost/wordpress/portfolio/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/AudreyHird-Mockup-768x432.jpg 768w, http://localhost/wordpress/portfolio/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/AudreyHird-Mockup-1024x576.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\" />											\n			<h1>Audrey Hird Alternative Therapies</h1>		\n			<h2>The Brief</h2>		\n		<p>The company made use of a self-created website. They felt that it had served its purpose and that it was time to move on to a professional website presence.</p><p>Audrey Hird Alternative Therapies requested that a business identity be created for them, which will encompass setting their corporate colours, creating a logo and developing a website that will provide their clients with a way to book treatments and/or training at a time of their choosing.</p><p>The current website must be replaced by a responsive website, reflecting their business identity and conveying a smart and professional image of the business.</p><p>The website need to act as the first point of contact with their customers, provide directions, contact form &amp; -details, connection to social media channels, an events calendar, a blog and ultimately be the main portal of booking appointments for customers.</p><p>It was very important that the colour scheme selected reflects the business and contributes to the connection with customers, whilst projecting a professional attitude.</p><p>The website had to be targeted to provide interaction with current customers and anyone who wants to recharge, relax or find alternative ways to manage stress and anxiety.</p>		\n										<img width=\"300\" height=\"300\" src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/portfolio/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/AHAT-Logo-300x300.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://localhost/wordpress/portfolio/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/AHAT-Logo-300x300.png 300w, http://localhost/wordpress/portfolio/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/AHAT-Logo-150x150.png 150w, http://localhost/wordpress/portfolio/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/AHAT-Logo-768x768.png 768w, http://localhost/wordpress/portfolio/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/AHAT-Logo-1024x1024.png 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" />											\n			<h2>User Personas</h2>		\n		<p>User Analysis research have identified the 2 main types of Users to be Treatment- and Training clients.</p><p>Their goals were almost identical, with only slight variations:</p><ul><li style=\"list-style-type: none;\"><ul><li>Need to see Treatment (<em>Training</em>), Duration &amp; Pricing information</li><li>Enquire about the availability of appointments and be able to reach out to the business via phone, email &amp; by submitting a contact form</li><li>Be able to book an appointment (<em>training class</em>) at a time suitable to them, without having to contact AHAT</li><li>Requires a confirmation email after booking their appointment and an email reminder before the scheduled appointment takes place.</li></ul></li></ul><p>Separate User Personas were created for Training - and Treatment customers.</p><p>Input from the customer themselves were used in the creation of these, as their previous website had no analytical functionality.</p>		\n										<img width=\"957\" height=\"902\" src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/portfolio/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/AHAT-Persona1.jpg\" alt=\"User Persona image\" srcset=\"http://localhost/wordpress/portfolio/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/AHAT-Persona1.jpg 957w, http://localhost/wordpress/portfolio/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/AHAT-Persona1-300x283.jpg 300w, http://localhost/wordpress/portfolio/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/AHAT-Persona1-768x724.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 957px) 100vw, 957px\" />											\n										<img width=\"957\" height=\"902\" src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/portfolio/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/AHAT-Persona2.jpg\" alt=\"User Persona image\" srcset=\"http://localhost/wordpress/portfolio/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/AHAT-Persona2.jpg 957w,